cially endemics related to agricultural crops, to contribute to food security; the deepening of knowledge about the goods and services of biological diversity; reforestation will continue to be an appropriate adaptive practice; In the case of pests and vectors, adaptation measures should be directed to counteract them with prevention policies that promote the use of organic techniques and mainly sanitary and sanitary measures Agriculture will develop in an environment affected by the increase in the frequency and intensity of droughts, the aridization of the climate, the decrease in real evapotranspiration of ecosystems and a pronounced water deficit. Net primary productivity and potential biomass density will decline; the duration in days of the phenological phases of important crops and the total duration of the crop cycles will be progressively shortened; and the potential returns will decrease. The combined scenarios of rising temperatures, falling rainfall, decreasing water potential and water quality, accompanied by the reduction of agricultural areas given the retreat of the coast and the migration of coastal ecosystems, will lead to higher impacts on total agricultural production and animal husbandry than those estimated by the direct impact of rising temperatures and reduced rainfall. In the agricultural sector, adaptation will require the use of technologies for the protection of crops and livestock; obtaining and introducing crop varieties with higher potential yields, as well as cattle breeds resistant to high temperatures and water deficit; and changes in the range of crops, which should be implemented as the climate evolves. The population will suffer the total impact of climate change, which will decrease their quality of life and increase the risk of certain extreme hydrometeorological diseases and events. This could manifest itself in different ways: the appearance of changes in the food culture of Cubans; also, for a significant number of people linked to agricultural and fishery production, there would be a transformation in e},
